data.description: Time to leave renting behind and start owning your very own well built 3 bedroom, 2.5 bath home with a monthly payments less than $2500. Seller has priced below recently appraised value!     This adorable home sits at the crossroads of Tucker, Clarkston, and Stone Mountain. You can get to downtown Decatur in 15 minutes or take a few steps and hop on the PATH. 1363 Oakengate is part of the Idlewood/Tucker School cluster.     Walk through the front door from the rocking chair front porch. To the left, the living room has a wood burning fireplace where you can forget about the stresses of your day. The large bay window lets the natural light pour in making it the best spot to chill out after a day at school or work.    The eat-in kitchen features stainless steel appliances, including a gas range. You'll enjoy cooking in the kitchen or grilling on the back patio while entertaining your friends. The solid wood cabinets have loads of storage for your favorite airfryer and amazing collection of coffee mugs.     On evenings that you are feeling fancy, host a game night or three course meal in the large dining room that overlooks the backyard. A table for 8 is no problemo so invite your friends & enjoy an evening of fun and laughter.     The owners have recently refinished the gorgeous wood floors that stretch throughout the first floor. They are impeccable and create a warm glow throughout the house as the sun hits them.     You'll find a powder room for your guests on the first floor so no more cleaning your bathroom counters off every time you have company.     Upstairs, the primary suite is big enough for a king sized bedroom suite. It has two closets and a private bathroom. The windows are south facing and provide the perfect lighting for your houseplant collection.     The guest bedrooms have large closets and plenty of natural light. These two bedrooms share a hall bath with the vanity and sink separated from the shower and toilet. It's perfect if you tire of hearing whose turn it is in the bathroom.     The backyard has the potential to be terraced and turned into the garden of your dreams and is the perfect size for a swings and a fort.    This not an HOA community but feels like it! Residents young and old take pride in their lawns and in each other. You'll spend your evenings on the front porch enjoying small talk with the dog walkers. Kids and adults love riding their bikes through this closed loop neighborhood and hitting the PATH to head into Clarkston for dinner.     Tucker is renovating their downtown with a massive green space and event schedule. (If you haven't, hit up the classic Matthew's Cafeteria!) Clarkston is adding (this winter!) 3 new restaurants, a new coffee shop, a co-working space, and a taco shop from the owner of DBA BBQ.     *** These photos have been virtually staged.
